int max (int, int)
	returns the maximum of the two arguments

int min (int a, int b)
	returns the minimum of the two arguments

typedef cv::Point3_<uint8_t> Pixel;
	Pixel is a structure with x, y, and z data members corresponding to the b, g and r values of the pixel.

Mat &CreateObjectMask(Mat &img) 
	creates object mask on the destination image in which objects are colored white and background black.
	returns the destination image.
	

	threshb, threshg, and threshr are lower limit BGR thresholds.
	threshbW, threshgW, and threshrW are upper limit BGR thresholds.
	alpha is the amount by which the images green channel is to be increased